arguments.description: A map of arguments used to configure the endpoint.

availabilityZone.description: The AWS availability zone where this endpoint is located.

extraJarsS3Path.description: Path to one or more Java Jars in an S3 bucket that should be loaded in this endpoint.

extraPythonLibsS3Path.description: Path(s) to one or more Python libraries in an S3 bucket that should be loaded in this endpoint. Multiple values must be complete paths separated by a comma.

failureReason.description: The reason for a current failure in this endpoint.

glueVersion.description: Specifies the versions of Python and Apache Spark to use. Defaults to AWS Glue version 0.9.

name.description: The name of this endpoint. It must be unique in your account.

numberOfWorkers.description: The number of workers of a defined worker type that are allocated to this endpoint. This field is available only when you choose worker type G.1X or G.2X.

privateAddress.description: A private IP address to access the endpoint within a VPC, if this endpoint is created within one.

publicAddress.description: The public IP address used by this endpoint. The PublicAddress field is present only when you create a non-VPC endpoint.

publicKey.description: The public key to be used by this endpoint for authentication.

publicKeys.description: A list of public keys to be used by this endpoint for authentication.

roleArn.description: The IAM role for this endpoint.

securityConfiguration.description: The name of the Security Configuration structure to be used with this endpoint.

securityGroupIds.description: Security group IDs for the security groups to be used by this endpoint.

status.description: The current status of this endpoint.

subnetId.description: The subnet ID for the new endpoint to use.

tagsAll.description: A map of tags assigned to the resource, including those inherited from the provider `default_tags` configuration block.

vpcId.description: he ID of the VPC used by this endpoint.

workerType.description: The type of predefined worker that is allocated to this endpoint. Accepts a value of Standard, G.1X, or G.2X.
